description: This chicken traybake recipe is brimming with autumn flavours. It’s an easy, hearty feed that’ll become a family favourite in no time.
name: Easy Chicken Traybake Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 4 chicken thigh cutlets, skin on, bone in
1 garlic bulb, cut in half horizontally

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Place chicken, skin-side down, in a cold non-stick frying pan over medium heat and cook for 8 minutes or until fat has rendered and skin is golden. Turn over and cook for a further 2 minutes.
Meanwhile, place pumpkin & sweet potato, onion, garlic, freekeh, stock, 1/2 cup water, spices and lemon zest in a large baking tray. Season, then stir to combine.

Nestle chicken, skin-side up, in tray. Cover with foil and bake for 25 minutes. Remove foil and cook for a further 15 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and freekeh is tender. Remove from oven and allow to rest for 10 minutes.
Stir through lemon juice and spinach, then serve.
